# P1 Touched-Surface Definition Of Done

- When touching a `P1` product surface, finish the product behavior and also review the touched path for foundation drift before calling the work complete.
- Limit cleanup to the files and flow you are already changing; do not start a repo-wide consistency refactor as part of unrelated product work.
- For changed routes and services, preserve or improve `P0` expectations in the touched path: tenant-safe auth/property scoping, validation, request tracing/logging, deterministic error handling, and health-aware dependency behavior.
- For cron jobs, outbound messaging, workflow actions, scoring, deploy/publish flows, or any other side-effecting path, add or update automated tests in the touched area.
- If the touched product path depends on files that belong in the trusted foundation surface, keep `p11-platform/apps/web/scripts/foundation-files.mjs` aligned.
- If the touched code uses a nonstandard Supabase client pattern, normalize it to the shared helpers in `p11-platform/apps/web/utils/supabase/` while you are there.
- If the work changes schema needs, follow the full schema-truth flow: verify with MCP, add/apply a migration, regenerate types, sync `p11-platform/apps/web/types/supabase.ts`, and stamp the migration version.
- If the touched change affects a critical local operator or user happy path, add or update local smoke coverage so the path stays reproducible.
- Prefer small opportunistic improvements in the touched product area over large framework-style abstractions unless the task explicitly calls for a broader refactor.
